               <p>511. <persName id="def1-511-18650508" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-511-18650508" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-511-18650508" type="age" value="30"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-511-18650508" type="surname" value="KELLY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-511-18650508" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">DANIEL KELLY</hi> (30)</persName>
                  <rs id="t18650508-511-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18650508-511-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18650508-511-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp>, Unlawfully uttering counterfeit coin.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CRAUFURD</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650508-name-84" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650508-name-84" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650508-name-84" type="surname" value="EDIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650508-name-84" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>SARAH EDIS</persName>
                  </hi>. On 17th April I was staying with my sister at 21, St.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="186505080013"></xptr>
               <p>George's-street—she sells tobacco—the prisoner came in that day, and I served him with half an ounce of tobacco, which came to three halfpence—he gave me a half-crown—I put it in the till—there was no other half-crown there—I gave him his change—I went to the till in half an hour, and found it was bad—he came again on 24th April, and I recognised him directly.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650508-name-85" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650508-name-85" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650508-name-85" type="surname" value="WISEMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650508-name-85" type="given" value="ESTHER"></interp>ESTHER WISEMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. My husband is a tobacconist—I am a sister of the last witness—on 24th of April the prisoner came for half an ounce of to<lb></lb>bacco, and gave me half a crown—I saw it was bad directly—he asked me to give it back to him, but I said, "I shall keep this"—he turned to go—I followed him, he took me by the arm at the door, and said, "Will you give me the half-brown?"—I said, "No"—I followed him to Mr. Girton's shop, where he said, "I am only looking for my partner"—I said to Mr. Girton, "This villain has passed three bad half-crowns in my shop in a fort<lb></lb>night" (I had taken three)—he ran away—Mr. Girton ran after him, and I saw him in custody ten minutes afterwards—I gave the half-crown to the constable—I found a bad half-crown in the till on 17th April, which I gave to my sister.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I plead guilty to that.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650508-name-86" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650508-name-86" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650508-name-86" type="surname" value="BRADLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650508-name-86" type="given" value="PHILIP"></interp>PHILIP BRADLEY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Policeman, H</hi> 59). I saw the prisoner running, followed by Mr. Girton—I stopped him and took him to the station, but found no money on him—I received this half-crown from Sarah Edis, and this other from Mrs. Wiseman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. WEBSTER</hi> These two half-crowns are bad, and from the same mould.</p>
